<inglise> Commission Regulation (EEC) No 1517/77 of 6 July 1977 fixing the list of the various groups of hop varieties cultivated in the Community </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 1517/77, millega kinnitatakse &uuml;henduses kasvatatud humalasortide r&uuml;hmade loetelu 6. juuli 1977 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1696/71 of 26 July 1971 on the common organization of the market in hops (1), as last amended by Regulation (EEC) No 1170/77 (2), and in particular Article 12 (8) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 26. juuli 1971. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/71 humalaturu &uuml;hise korralduse kohta, viimati muudetud m&auml;&auml;rusega (EM&Uuml;) nr 1170/77, eriti selle artikli 12 l&otilde;iget 8, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas, with effect from the 1977 harvest, pursuant to Article 12 (5) of Regulation (EEC) No 1696/71, production aid for hops will differ according to group of varieties; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: koosk&otilde;las m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/71 artikli 12 l&otilde;ikega 5 erineb alates 1977. aasta saagikoristusest humalale antav tootmistoetus vastavalt sordir&uuml;hmale; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas these groups, three in number, are defined according to commercial practice on the Community and world hop market on the basis of the final use of the hops in brewing by reference to common characteristics, with the emphasis placed on the content of bitter and aromatic substances; whereas for this reason the varieties of hop cultivated in the Community must be classified into the groups "aromatic hops", "bitter hops" and "others"; </inglise>
<eesti> kolm k&otilde;nealust r&uuml;hma m&auml;&auml;ratletakse koosk&otilde;las &uuml;henduse ja maailma humalaturul kehtivate kaubandustavadega selle p&otilde;hjal, millised on sortide &uuml;hised omadused l&otilde;ppkasutuse korral pruulimisel, v&otilde;ttes eriti arvesse m&otilde;ruainete ja aromaatainete sisaldust; selleks tuleb &uuml;henduses kasvatatud humalasordid liigitada r&uuml;hmadesse "aromaatne humal", "m&otilde;ru humal" ja "muu"; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Hops, </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las humalaturu korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Sole Article </inglise>
<eesti> Ainus artikkel </eesti>
<inglise> The list of varieties of hops in the groups "aromatic hops", "bitter hops" and "other" varieties, within the meaning of Article 12 (5) of Regulation (EEC) No 1696/71, is set out in the Annex hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> R&uuml;hmade "aromaatne humal", "m&otilde;ru humal" ja "muud" humalasortide loetelu m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1696/71 t&auml;henduses on s&auml;testatud k&auml;esoleva m&auml;&auml;ruse lisas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 6 July 1977. </inglise>
<eesti> Br&uuml;ssel, 6. juuli 1977 </eesti>
<inglise> For the Commission Finn GUNDELACH Vice-President </inglise>
<eesti> Komisjoni nimel asepresident Finn GUNDELACH </eesti>
 